---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for Customer Acquisition in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for permissioned acquisition, source-aware welcome journeys, paid traffic follow-up, and cohort measurement.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Acquisition programs with rich data','Useful for source, behavior, product, and engagement segmentation.','Profile cost and attribution complexity increase with scale.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/signup-forms'],['Omnisend','Commerce teams converting new audiences','A practical fit for forms, welcome journeys, and ecommerce automation.','Incentive and channel rules need discipline.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/'],['Sequenzy','Lean teams building owned relationships','Good for a focused welcome sequence after a clear, permissioned signup.','Advanced source attribution should be verified.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Brevo','Broad acquisition and campaign operations','Useful for forms, campaigns, and automation in one stack.','Consent and source data mapping need QA.','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small stores starting with owned acquisition','A simple native option for basic forms and welcome campaigns.','Less suited to complex paid-source branches.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Customer acquisition is complete only when a new contact becomes a healthy, permissioned relationship. Email should carry context from the source and earn attention after the first signup.</p><p>Measure qualified opt-in, welcome engagement, first-order conversion, payback, unsubscribe rate, and cohort retention. Use a consistent source taxonomy and avoid treating every acquired address as equal simply because it entered the same list.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for customer acquisition</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[0]} is useful when acquisition source can change the welcome message, incentive, or next action without compromising consent. Build a cohort view that follows subscribers beyond the first order, and remove or sunset contacts that never engage. Acquisition quality is ultimately a retention and margin question.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Check current contacts, forms, sends, automation, and attribution limits; paid acquisition can expand profile cost quickly.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Question</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Who joined?</td><td>Source and consent context</td><td>Qualified opt-in</td></tr><tr><td>What happened next?</td><td>Welcome and product relevance</td><td>First-order conversion</td></tr><tr><td>Was it worthwhile?</td><td>Cohort and margin reporting</td><td>Payback and retention</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Explore <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, review <a href="/use-cases/welcome-series">welcome-series use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
